An $({\alpha} \mid {\beta})$\emph{-co-intersection representation} (CIR) for a graph ${\mathcal G} = ({\mathcal V},{\mathcal E})$ is a family
${\mathscr{L}} = \{(A_v \mid B_v): v \in {\mathcal V}\}$, where $A_v \subseteq {\mathcal A}$, $B_v \subseteq {\mathcal B}$, that satisfies 
the so-called \emph{Co-Intersection Condition}:\vspace{-5pt}

